data.name: ErrorCode_00055
data.value: X-Ray OFF signal open to power up

data.name: ErrorDesc_00002
data.value: Displayed if an internal computation results in a division by zero. Requires power to be recycled.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00003
data.value: Displayed if an internal computation results in a division by zero. Requires power to be recycled.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00004
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator kV exceeds the desired value. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00005
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator mA exceeds the desired value. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00009
data.value: Generator error. Displayed after power up if the sense of a dual focal spot filament setting changes.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00010
data.value: Generator error. Displayed after power up if the sense of an anode tank changes.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00011
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator kV exceeds a value set in the combination of X-Ray tube and generator data. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00012
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator mA exceeds a value set in the combination of X-Ray tube and generator data. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00013
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when an internal current limit is exceeded in the generator drive electronics. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00014
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when an internal voltage limit is exceeded in the generator drive electronics. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00015
data.value: Displayed when the coolant flow rate is less than the internal setting. Non-latching error; will reset automatically. This error disconnects the safety contactor.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00016
data.value: Displayed when the coolant temperature exceeds the internal cooler limit. Non-latching error; will reset automatically. This error disconnects the safety contactor.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00018
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator kV fails to reach the desired value within a defined period of time. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00019
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator mA fails to reach the desired value within a defined period of time. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00022
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the decay of the kV at the end of the exposure takes too long. The system status will remain as X-Ray ON until the kV threshold is reached.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00024
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the generator kV exceeds a certain value in X-Ray OFF.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00025
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the generator mA exceeds a certain value in X-Ray OFF.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00027
data.value: Displayed if the communications from the generator fails. This will inhibit or terminate X-Rays ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00028
data.value: Displayed when all filters are in the wall box when a filter is selected (only certain systems). Non-latching error; will reset automatically.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00029
data.value: Displayed when more than one filter is missing from the wall box when a filter is selected (only certain systems). Non-latching error; will reset automatically.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00030
data.value: Displayed when no filter is fitted to the sub-tube assembly when a filter is selected. Non-latching error; will reset automatically.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00034
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems when the anode and cathode kV measurements differ by a defined amount. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00035
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems when the anode and cathode mA measurements differ by a defined amount. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00036
data.value: Generator error. Displayed whilst the connection to the control PCB from the filament feedback PCB is open circuit (CP Models).

data.name: ErrorDesc_00037
data.value: Generator error. Displayed whilst the heatseat sink thermostat indicates a high temperature.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00038
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the value of calibration voltage entered in an initializing process is too high.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00039
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the value of calibration voltage entered in an initializing process is too low.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00040
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems when the anode tank mA exceeds the desired value. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00041
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems when the anode tank mA fails to reach the desired value within a defined period of time. Latching error

data.name: ErrorDesc_00042
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when the generator fails to reach 5 kV within a defined period of time after receiving an X-Ray ON command. Latching error

data.name: ErrorDesc_00043
data.value: Generator error. Displayed when an exposure is terminated by the removal of the interlock input to the generator. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00045
data.value: Displayed when the time entered in a Time treatment exceeds the set time limit. This error will persist until a compliant time is entered. (can be caused in a Dose treatment)

data.name: ErrorDesc_00046
data.value: Displayed when an uninitialized filter is selected or zero values detected for any of the following: kV, mA, HVL, Type HVL, Dimension or encoding.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00047
data.value: Displayed when an uninitialized applicator is selected; non-valid shape or zero values in any of the following: width, breadth for rectangular applicator, length or encoding.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00048
data.value: Displayed when a filter is selected for a dose exposure with a non-valid reference applicator or zero values for counts/second or counts/MU.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00049
data.value: Displayed when the X-Ray button is pressed and the internal NEEDS status indicates the exposure is not set. This error will persist until another treatment is set.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00050
data.value: Displayed when the X-Ray button is pressed and the internal NEEDS status indicates the filter is not set. This error will persist until another treatment is set.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00051
data.value: Displayed when the X-Ray button is pressed and the internal NEEDS status indicates the applicator is not set. This error will persist until another treatment is set.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00052
data.value: Displayed when the temperature (in degrees centrigrade) read from the transducer is less than a minimum (10) or greater than a maximum (35). Dose systems only. This error will persist whilst the temperature is invalid.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00053
data.value: Displayed when the pressure (in milli-bars) read from the transducer is less than a minimum (700) or greater than a maximum (1200). Dose systems only. This error will persist while the pressure is invalid.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00055
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray OFF button is open-circuit at power up.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00056
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped by the door contact being open. Latching error requires a new X-Ray ON signal to be reset.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00057
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped by the second door/room interlock contact being opened. Latching error requiring a new X-Ray ON signal to be reset.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00058
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped by the cooler flow contact being opened. Latching error requiring a new X-Ray ON signal to be reset.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00059
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped by the cooler temp contact being opened. Latching error requiring a new X-Ray ON signal to be reset.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00060
data.value: Displayed at start-up if the safety contactor is engaged but not enabled.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00064
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the processor in the generator has reset.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00066
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped by the control pod key being moved from HT (position 3), the X-Ray enable position. Non-latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00072
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the digital to analog converter (DAC) offset voltage is too high. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00073
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the digital to analog converter (DAC) range data is incorrect. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00074
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the analog to digital converter (ADC) offset voltage is too high. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00075
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the analog to digital converter (ADC) range data is incorrect. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00076
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the analog to digital converter (ADC) calibration is lost. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00077
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the generator type data is corrupt. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00078
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the X-Rays have been terminated by three events at successively lower kV values. This will inhibit an exposure.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00079
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the generator receives an X-Ray ON initiation, but the X-Ray OFF interlock line is not enabled (sourced with current).

data.name: ErrorDesc_00080
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems if the decay of the anode kV at the end of the exposure takes too long. The system status will remain as X-Ray ON until the kV threshold is reached.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00081
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if an exposure is terminated by the loss of the interlock signal. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00082
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if an exposure is terminated by the heatsink thermostat. Latching error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00083
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the unipolar or bipolar tables are incompatible.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00084
data.value: Displayed if the two door sensors fail to operate together when configured to do so. This will prevent X-Ray ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00085
data.value: Generator error. Not used in this system.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00087
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems if the anode generator tank kV exceeds a certain value in X-Ray OFF.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00088
data.value: Generator error. Displayed in bipolar systems if the anode generator tank mA exceeds a certain value in X-Ray OFF.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00089
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the mA measured remains at zero after a specified time.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00091
data.value: Generator error. Latching error. Displayed if a residual kV error has terminated X-Rays.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00092
data.value: Generator error. Latching error. Displayed if a residual mA error has terminated X-Rays.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00107
data.value: Displayed if the control of the interlock relay does not result in the correct response from the generator.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00108
data.value: Displayed when the applicator is selected for a Dose exposure and the applicator factor for the selected applicator is out of range. (Must be greater than or equal to 0.8 and less than or equal to 1.2.)

data.name: ErrorDesc_00109
data.value: Displayed when the dose entered in a Dose treatment exceeds the set dose limit. This error will persist until a compliant dose is entered.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00110
data.value: Displayed if the TP2 fails to read data from the LCD. This error will persist until rectified.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00111
data.value: Displayed when the dose rate monitored in a Dose treatment is less than the calibrated dose rate by more than 3%. The ratio of actual mA to desired mA will be used to modify the calculation on the switch on mA ramp. The error will terminate X-Rays. The error requires the control pod key to be counter-rotated to standby (position 2) and then back to HT (position 3) to clear before X-Rays are enabled.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00112
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped by the Emergency OFF button being pressed. X-Rays will not automatically resume after the Emergency OFF has been manually reset, but may after the X-Ray ON button is pressed.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00113
data.value: Displayed if the external Power ON lamp fails to draw current. This will prevent X-Ray ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00114
data.value: Displayed if the external X-Ray ON lamp fails to draw current. This will terminate X-Ray ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00115
data.value: Displayed when the X-Ray button is pressed and the internal NEEDS status indicates the program is not set. This error will persist until another treatment is set.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00116
data.value: Displayed if the X-Ray beam is stopped because the control pod key has been moved from HT (position 3), the enable position. Latching error requires new X-Ray ON signal to be reset.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00117
data.value: Displayed when the program monitoring the TP2 through the series communications fails to receive data. The program will indicate POWER LOST and wait for the TP2 to recover and, if possible, resume. Resumption of X-Rays will only be possible by operator control.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00118
data.value: Displayed if the generator mA limit (for the desired kV) is less than the required Treatment mA. This will prevent X-Rays ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00119
data.value: Displayed if the generator kV limit is less than the required Treatment kV. This will prevent X-Rays ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00120
data.value: Displayed when the exposure is stopped by the backup timer. The calculation of the limit will vary between Time and Dose treatments. No further exposure is allowed. X-Rays ON will be allowed, but termination will be repeated as soon as the timer starts.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00121
data.value: Displayed when the dose rate monitored in a Dose treatment is greater than the calibrated dose rate by more than 3%. The error will terminate X-Rays. The error requires the control pod key to be counter-rotated to standby (position 2) and then back to HT (position 3) to clear before the X-Rays are enabled.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00122
data.value: Displayed when the applicator bits do not match those of the specified applicator.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00123
data.value: Displayed when the filter bits do not match those of the specified filter.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00124
data.value: Displayed if the generator does not turn OFF within 2 seconds.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00125
data.value: Displayed if the generator does not turn ON within 2 seconds.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00127
data.value: Displayed if the generator cannot be set to the required kV or mA. This will prevent X-Rays ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00129
data.value: Generator error. Displayed if the current date exceeds the date chosen for routine maintenance. Will not inhibit X-Rays ON.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00193
data.value: Displayed when the interlock to the generator is open; suppressed unless the interlock relay is enabled.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00195
data.value: Displayed when the TP2 fails to receive a software interlock from the PC at less than one second intervals with the control pod key in HT (position 3).

data.name: ErrorDesc_00196
data.value: Displayed when the first safety signal is not sensed at the TP2. This error will disconnect the safety contactor.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00197
data.value: Displayed when the second safety signal is not sensed at the TP2. This error will disconnect the safety contactor.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00228
data.value: Displayed when the TP2 software fails to re-trigger the watchdog in time. The error is not resettable. Fatal error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00229
data.value: Displayed when the TP2 background software fails to execute in time. The error is not resettable. Fatal error.

data.name: ErrorDesc_00234
data.value: Displayed if an unexpected fault occurs. The error is not resettable. Fatal error

data.name: ErrorDesc_00236
data.value: Displayed if a bad instruction is detected. The error is not resettable. Fatal error

data.name: ErrorDesc_00243
data.value: Displayed if an internal processor clock fault arises. The error is not resettable. Fatal error.
